#: ../../source/network/route.rst:2
msgid "路由算法"
msgstr "Routing Algorithms"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:5
msgid "简介"
msgstr "Introduction"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:6
msgid ""
"路由算法是用于找到一条从源路由器到目的路由器的最佳路径的算法。存在着多种路由算法，每种算法对网络和路由器资源的影响都不同；由于路由算法使用多种度量标准"
" (metric)，所以不同路由算法的最佳路径选择也有所不同。"
msgstr "A routing algorithm is an algorithm used to find the best path from a source router to a destination router. Many routing algorithms exist, and each affects network and router resources differently. Because routing algorithms use different metrics, their best-path selections can also differ."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:9
msgid "路由选择算法的功能"
msgstr "Functions of Routing Algorithms"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:10
msgid "源/宿对之间的路径选择，以及选定路由之后将报文传送到它们的目的地。"
msgstr "Selecting paths between source/destination pairs and forwarding packets to their destinations after a route has been selected."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:12
msgid "路由选择算法的要求："
msgstr "Requirements for routing algorithms:"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:14
msgid "正确性：确保分组从源节点传送到目的节点"
msgstr "Correctness: ensure that packets are delivered from the source node to the destination node"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:15
msgid "简单性：实现方便，软硬件开销小"
msgstr "Simplicity: easy to implement, with low software and hardware overhead"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:16
msgid "自适应性：也称健壮性，算法能够适应业务量和网络拓扑的变化"
msgstr "Adaptability: also called robustness, meaning the algorithm can adapt to changes in traffic volume and network topology"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:17
msgid "稳定性：能长时间无故障运行"
msgstr "Stability: can run for long periods without failure"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:18
msgid "公平性：每个节点都有机会传送信息"
msgstr "Fairness: every node has an opportunity to transmit information"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:19
msgid "最优性：尽量选取好的路由"
msgstr "Optimality: choose good routes as much as possible"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:22
msgid "自治系统 AS (Autonomous System)"
msgstr "Autonomous System (AS)"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:23
msgid "经典定义："
msgstr "Classic definition:"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:25
msgid "由一个组织管理的一整套路由器和网络。"
msgstr "A set of routers and networks managed by one organization."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:26
msgid "使用一种AS 内部的路由选择协议和共同的度量以确定分组在该 AS 内的路由。"
msgstr "It uses an intra-AS routing protocol and a common metric to determine routes for packets within that AS."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:27
msgid "使用一种 AS 之间的路由选择协议用以确定分组在AS之间的路由。"
msgstr "It uses an inter-AS routing protocol to determine routes for packets between ASes."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:29
msgid "尽管一个 AS 使用了多种内部路由选择协议和度量，但对其他 AS 表现出的是一个单一的和一致的路由选择策略。"
msgstr "Although an AS may use multiple internal routing protocols and metrics, it presents a single and consistent routing policy to other ASes."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:32
msgid "两大类路由选择协议"
msgstr "Two Major Categories of Routing Protocols"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:33
msgid ""
"因特网的中，路由协议可以分为内部网关协议 IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol)和外部网关协议 EGP (External"
" Gateway Protocol)。"
msgstr "On the Internet, routing protocols can be divided into Interior Gateway Protocols (IGP) and Exterior Gateway Protocols (EGP)."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:35
msgid ""
"IGP是在一个AS内部使用的路由选择协议，如RIP和OSPF协议，是域内路由选择 (interdomain "
"routing)。当源主机和目的主机处在不同的AS中，在数据报到达AS的边界时，使用外部网关协议 EGP "
"将路由选择信息传递到另一个自治系统中，如BGP-4，是域间路由选择 (intradomain routing)。"
msgstr "IGP is a routing protocol used inside one AS, such as RIP and OSPF, and is used for intradomain routing. When the source host and destination host are in different ASes, an Exterior Gateway Protocol (EGP), such as BGP-4, passes routing information to another autonomous system when a datagram reaches the AS boundary; this is interdomain routing."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:38
msgid "RIP"
msgstr "RIP"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:39
msgid ""
"路由信息协议 (Routing Information Protocol, RIP) 是一种基于距离 向量的路由选择协议。RIP "
"协议要求网络中的每一个路由器都要维护从它自己到自治系统内其他每一个目的网络的距离和下一跳路由器地址。"
msgstr "Routing Information Protocol (RIP) is a distance-vector-based routing protocol. RIP requires every router in the network to maintain the distance from itself to every other destination network within the autonomous system and the address of the next-hop router."

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:42
msgid "OSPF"
msgstr "OSPF"

#: ../../source/network/route.rst:43
msgid ""
"开放最短路径优先(Open Shortest Path First，OSPF)，这个算法名为“最短路径优先”是因为使用了 Dijkstra "
"提出的最短路径算法SPF，只是一个协议的名字，它并不表示其他的路由选择协议不是“最短路径优先”。"
msgstr "Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) is named \"Shortest Path First\" because it uses Dijkstra's SPF shortest-path algorithm. It is only the name of the protocol and does not imply that other routing protocols are not shortest-path-first protocols."
